{"title_page": "Ku-Ku Band", "text_new": "{{Infobox musical artist\n| name            = Ku-Ku Band\n| image           = \n| image_size      = \n| image_upright   = \n| landscape       = \n| alt             = \n| caption         = \n| background      = band\n| alias           = \n| origin          = {{flag|Bulgaria}}\n| genre           = mainly [[pop-folk]], also [[folk music]], [[pop music]] and ethno rock music\n| years_active    = {{Start date|1993}}\u2013present\n| label           = [[Bulgarian Music Compan]]y, [[Seven-Eight Production]]\n| associated_acts = [[Sofi Marinova]], [[Krisko]], [[Desi Dobreva]]\n| website         = <!-- {{URL|example.com}} or {{Official URL}} -->\n| current_members = [[Slavi Trifonov]], frontman <br/> Evgeni Dimitrov, [[Synthesizer|keyboards]] <br/> Georgi Milchev \u2013 Godzhi, [[bass guitar]] <br/> Cvetan Nedyalkov, [[Electrical guitar|solo guitar]] <br/> Iliya Iliev, [[clarinet]] <br/> Evgeni Yotov, [[saxophone]] <br/> Yordan Yonchev, [[trumpet]] <br/> Venelin Venkov, [[drums]] and [[percussions]] <br/> Reydi Machado Brizuela, percussions <br/> Ivan Stoyanov, rhythm guitar <br/> Kristian Iliev, keyboards <br/> Boris Soltariyski, vocal <br/> Liliya Stefanova, vocal <br/> Nevena Tsoneva, vocal \n| past_members    = \n| module          = \n| module2         = \n| module3         = \n}}\n'''Ku-Ku band''' ([[Bulgarian language|Bulgarian]]: ''\u041a\u0443-\u041a\u0443 \u0431\u0435\u043d\u0434'') is [[Bulgaria|Bulgarian]] mainly [[pop-folk]] musical group established on 1993. First group members were [[Slavi Trifonov]], [[Evgeni Dimitrov]] \u2013 ''The Maestro'', [[Evgeni Yotov]] and [[Iliya Iliev (musician)|Iliya Iliev]]. \n\nDuring 19 years of existence of the [[Slavi's Show]] (Bulgarian: ''\u0428\u043e\u0443\u0442\u043e \u043d\u0430 \u0421\u043b\u0430\u0432\u0438'') on [[BTV (Bulgaria)|bTV]], the band had appearance on scene as musical part of the show. In that period the band together with its frontman published 12 albums, 77 singles, or total 247 songs. Also the band had 7 tours in Bulgaria, [[Greece]], [[Canada]] and [[USA]] and had over 100 concerts during tours and also out of the tours in [[Spain]] and the [[United Kingdom]]. During the show broadcasting, Ku-Ku Band had its own section called ''Band's Hour'' (''\u0427\u0430\u0441\u044a\u0442 \u043d\u0430 \u0431\u0435\u043d\u0434\u0430'') where the main theme of that show's episode was the band and their members.<ref name=\"tvor\">{{cite web|url=https://www.slavishow.com/\u0442\u0432\u043e\u0440\u0447\u0435\u0441\u0442\u0432\u043e\u0442\u043e-\u043d\u0430-\u043a\u0443-\u043a\u0443-\u0431\u0435\u043d\u0434/|title=\u0422\u0432\u043e\u0440\u0447\u0435\u0441\u0442\u0432\u043e\u0442\u043e \u043d\u0430 \u201e\u041a\u0443-\u043a\u0443 \u0431\u0435\u043d\u0434\u201c|publisher=Slavi's Show Official Site|language=Bulgarian}}</ref><ref name=\"slavishow3007\">{{cite web|url=https://www.slavishow.com/\u0448\u043e\u0443\u0442\u043e-\u043d\u0430-\u0441\u043b\u0430\u0432\u0438-30-\u044e\u043b\u0438-2019-\u0433/|title=\u0428\u043e\u0443\u0442\u043e \u043d\u0430 \u0421\u043b\u0430\u0432\u0438, 30 \u044e\u043b\u0438 2019 \u0433.|publisher=Slavi's Show Official Site|language=Bulgarian}}</ref> Later it started appearing on [[Evening Show of Slavi Trifonov]] (Bulgarian: ''\u0412\u0435\u0447\u0435\u0440\u043d\u043e\u0442\u043e \u0448\u043e\u0443 \u043d\u0430 \u0421\u043b\u0430\u0432\u0438 \u0422\u0440\u0438\u0444\u043e\u043d\u043e\u0432'') on [[7/8 TV]] as successor of the previous show on bTV.<ref name=\"sedemosmi\">{{cite web|url=https://sedemosmi.tv/\u043f\u0440\u0435\u0434\u0430\u0432\u0430\u043d\u0438\u044f/\u0432\u0435\u0447\u0435\u0440\u043d\u043e\u0442\u043e-\u0448\u043e\u0443-\u043d\u0430-\u0441\u043b\u0430\u0432\u0438-\u0442\u0440\u0438\u0444\u043e\u043d\u043e\u0432/|title=\u0412\u0435\u0447\u0435\u0440\u043d\u043e\u0442\u043e \u0448\u043e\u0443 \u043d\u0430 \u0421\u043b\u0430\u0432\u0438 \u0422\u0440\u0438\u0444\u043e\u043d\u043e\u0432|publisher=7/8 TV Official Site|language=Bulgarian}}</ref> Till today, the band published 23 albums.<ref name=\"disk\">{{cite web|url=https://www.slavishow.com/\u0434\u0438\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0433\u0440\u0430\u0444\u0438\u044f/|title=\u0414\u0438\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0433\u0440\u0430\u0444\u0438\u044f|publisher=Slavi's Show Official Site|language=Bulgarian}}</ref><ref name=\"78disk\">{{cite web|url=https://sedemosmi.tv/\u0434\u0438\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0433\u0440\u0430\u0444\u0438\u044f/|title=\u0414\u0438\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0433\u0440\u0430\u0444\u0438\u044f|publisher=7/8 TV Official Site|language=Bulgarian}}</ref>\n\n== Discography ==\n* \"''\u0420\u044a\u0433\u0430\u0439 \u0447\u0443\u0448\u043a\u0438 \u0432 \u0431\u043e\u0431\u0430''\" (''R\u0103gay chushki v boba'', ''\"Poke peppers into bean\"''), 1993\n* \"''\u0428\u0430\u0442 \u043d\u0430 \u043f\u0430\u0442\u043a\u0430\u0442\u0430 \u0433\u043b\u0430\u0432\u0430\u0442\u0430''\" (''Shat na patkata glavata''), 1994\n* \"''\u0420\u043e\u043c\u0430 TV''\" (''Roma TV''), 1994\n* \"''\u0416\u044a\u043b\u0442\u0430 \u043a\u043d\u0438\u0436\u043a\u0430''\" (''Zh\u0103lta knizhka'', ''\"Yellow Book\"''), 1995, BMK\n* \"''\u0425\u044a\u0448\u043e\u0432\u0435''\" (''H\u0103shove'', ''\"Outcasts\"''), 1996, BMK\n* \"''\u041a\u0430\u043d\u0430\u043b\u0435\u0442\u043e The Best''\" (''Kanaleto''), 1997, BMK\n* \"''\u0415\u0434\u043d\u043e \u0444\u0435\u0440\u0430\u0440\u0438 \u0441 \u0446\u0432\u044f\u0442 \u0447\u0435\u0440\u0432\u0435\u043d''\" (''Edno ferari s cvyat cherven'', ''\"A Red Colored Ferrari\"''), 1997, BMK\n* \"''\u0424\u0440\u0430\u043d\u0446\u0438\u044f, \u0437\u0434\u0440\u0430\u0432\u0435\u0439''\" (''Frantsiya, zdravey'', ''\"Hello France\"''), 1998, BMK\n* \"''\u0414\u0435\u0432\u0435\u0442\u0438 \u0442\u0440\u0430\u0433\u0438\u0447\u0435\u043d''\" (''Deveti tragichen'', ''\"The Ninth Tragic\"''), 1998, BMK\n* \"''\u0412\u0430\u0432\u0438\u043b\u043e\u043d''\" (''Vavilon'', \"''Babylon''\"), 1998/99, BMK\n* \"''\u041d\u044f\u043c\u0430 \u201e\u043d\u0435 \u0438\u0441\u043a\u0430\u043c\u201c''\" (''Nyama \"ne iskam\"'', ''\"There's no 'I don't want it'\"''), 1999, BMK\n* \"''\u0427\u0430\u0441\u044a\u0442 \u043d\u0430 \u0431\u0435\u043d\u0434\u0430''\" (''Chas\u0103t na benda'', ''\"The Band's Hour\"''), 2000, BMK\n* \"''\u041d\u043e\u0432\u0438\u0442\u0435 \u0432\u0430\u0440\u0432\u0430\u0440\u0438''\" (''Novite varvari'', ''\"New Barbarians\"''), 2001, BMK\n* \"''The Best''\", compilation, 2002, BMK\n* \"''Vox populi''\", 2003\n* \"''\u041f\u0440\u0438\u043c\u0430 \u043f\u0430\u0442\u0440\u0438\u043e\u0442''\" (''Prima patriot''), 2004\n* \"''\u0418 \u043e\u0440\u043a\u0435\u0441\u0442\u044a\u0440\u0430 \u0434\u0430 \u0441\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0438''\" (''I orkest\u0103ra da sviri'', ''\"And Orchestra to Play\"''), 2005\n* \"''\u041d\u0438\u0435 \u043f\u0440\u043e\u0434\u044a\u043b\u0436\u0430\u0432\u0430\u043c\u0435''\" (''Nie prod\u0103lzhavame'', ''\"We continue\"''), 2007\n* \"''No Mercy''\", 2009, Seven-Eight Production\n* \"''\u041c\u0430\u043a\u0435\u0434\u043e\u043d\u0438\u044f''\" (''Makedoniya'', ''\"Macedonia\"''), 2010, Seven-Eight Production\n* \"''\u0415\u0434\u0438\u043d \u043e\u0442 \u043c\u043d\u043e\u0433\u043e\u0442\u043e''\" (Edin ot mnogoto, \"One of Many\"), 2012\n* \"''\u0418\u043c\u0430 \u0442\u0430\u043a\u044a\u0432 \u043d\u0430\u0440\u043e\u0434''\" (''Ima tak\u0103v narod'', ''\"There is such a nation\"''), 2017\n* \"''\u041f\u0435\u0441\u043d\u0438 \u0437\u0430 \u0431\u044a\u043b\u0433\u0430\u0440\u0438''\" (''Pesni za b\u0103lgari'', ''\"Songs for Bulgarians\"''), 2018\n\n== See also ==\n* [[Slavi Trifonov]]\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Musical groups established in 1993]]\n[[Category:Bulgarian musical groups]]\n[[Category:Bulgarian music]]\n[[Category:1993 establishments in Bulgaria]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox musical artist\n| name            = Ku-Ku Band\n| image           = \n| image_size      = \n| image_upright   = \n| landscape      